<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t16870406-14">
               <interp inst="t16870406-14" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16870406-14" type="year" value="1687"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16870406-14" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/16870406"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16870406-14" type="date" value="16870406"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16870406-14-off72-c65" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870406-14-defend92 t16870406-14-off72 t16870406-14-verdict75"></join>
         
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t16870406-14-defend92" type="defendantName">
                  Humphry 
                  Burton
               <interp inst="t16870406-14-defend92" type="surname" value="Burton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-defend92" type="given" value="Humphry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-defend92" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , was Tryed for <rs id="t16870406-14-off72" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-off72" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-off72" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a Frise Coat valu'd at 40 s. and a Hatt valu'd 10 s.
            </rs> from 
               <persName id="t16870406-14-victim93" type="victimName">
                  Thomas 
                  Waight
               <interp inst="t16870406-14-victim93" type="surname" value="Waight"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-victim93" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-victim93" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870406-14-off72 t16870406-14-victim93"></join>
                  </persName>
             Junior, of the Parish of <placeName id="t16870406-14-crimeloc73">St. Anne Blackfryers</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16870406-14-crimeloc73" type="placeName" value="St. Anne Blackfryers"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16870406-14-crimeloc73" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870406-14-off72 t16870406-14-crimeloc73"></join> on the <rs id="t16870406-14-cd74" type="crimeDate">23d. of December</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870406-14-off72 t16870406-14-cd74"></join> last, the Evidence against him was 
               <persName id="t16870406-14-person94">
                  Thomas 
                  Waight
               <interp inst="t16870406-14-person94" type="surname" value="Waight"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-person94" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-person94" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and 
               <persName id="t16870406-14-person95">
                  Robert 
                  Waight
               <interp inst="t16870406-14-person95" type="surname" value="Waight"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-person95" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-person95" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who deposed they met him in the street with the Coat upon his Back, and there Challenged it, the which Coat was likewise produced and owned by them in Court but he in his own defence pleading he bought it of one 
               <persName id="t16870406-14-person96">
                  John 
                  Green
               <interp inst="t16870406-14-person96" type="surname" value="Green"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-person96" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-person96" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , since dead, and bringing Green's Wife to Testifie that it was her Husbands Coat and that he had sold it him, the Jury <rs id="t16870406-14-verdict75" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870406-14-verdict75" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs> him.</p>
            </div1>
